This cleanup is great, thanks! I have made several suggestions that might help further.
Is there any reason not to set a `socket-id` for the first port? That would stop this from being a special case.

Because we only use ipmi sol for cpu console and phosphor-net-ipmid uses the same default socket-id as obmc-console and phosphor-hostlogger, so I leave it empty for the cpu console configs in 3 recipes for automatic mapping, as we don't know if we are going to continue to support more consoles than just cpu's.

Rather than copy/pasting the upstream service unit, can you add a systemd drop-in unit to add the ExecStartPre line? Then you could drop this file entirely and use the upstream obmc-console service unit. You could model your drop-in on `use-socket.conf` from obmc-console.
The uart setting has to done anyway so we decided to move them to platform init, so the original service file is used now.
I think some of this can be cleaned up by using `OBMC_CONSOLE_TTYS` from https://github.com/openbmc/openbmc/blob/master/meta-phosphor/recipes-phosphor/console/obmc-console_git.bb#L78-L80
Done

how's about removing this script and add codes similar to below to ampere_platform_init.sh?

for i in 1..4
do
  /usr/sbin/ampere_uartmux_ctrl.sh $i 2
done
Because I want anyone looking at this can see the relation between this and obmc-console ttys. Does this necessarily have to be changed for time and resource saving purpose?
